  "market_context": "Bullish market structure with break of structure up, followed by pullback into discount zone (below 50% Fib) coinciding with a well-formed Fair Value Gap. Analyst waited for 1-minute timeframe shift at London open for confirmation.",
  "key_observation": "Price entered a discount zone containing a mitigated Fair Value Gap; aggressive bullish 1-minute candle at London open confirmed the long setup.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified swing high and swing low to confirm bullish break of structure on 1H chart.",
    "Step 2: Drew Fibonacci retracement from recent low to high and defined discount zone as price below 50% level.",
    "Step 3: Located a well-formed Fair Value Gap within the discount zone, refined to the most recent unmitigated portion.",
    "Step 4: Zoomed into 1-minute timeframe once price entered the FVG/discount confluence zone.",
    "Step 5: Waited for bullish shift on 1-minute chart—specifically an aggressive bullish candle—at the start of London open for confirmation.",
    "Step 6: Executed long entry at open of the 1-minute FVG, placed stop loss below the FVG low, and targeted the prior swing high for 1:3 risk-reward."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade executed as described; analyst noted it would have yielded 1:3 RR (and potentially >1:5 with tighter stop), but emphasized this was a *demonstration* trade—not the main case he intended to break down. No explicit outcome shown for this specific long setup in the transcript.",
  "lessons": "Refining entries to lower timeframes (e.g., 1M FVG) within confluence zones (FVG + discount) increases precision and risk-reward. Waiting for session-specific confirmation (London open) improves win rate over impulsive breakout trades.",
